  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UoA evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is limited to pre-market credibility submission for worst-case operating-point identification; not intended for patient-specific dosing or real-time control. Scope is restricted to adult CPB flows between 3–7 L/min and rotational speeds 1500–3500 RPM.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-credible",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-hemolysis-bench"
  ],
